## Part X: Conclusion

The thermodynamic derivation of gravity has been incomplete for 30 years because relativistic thermodynamics textbooks made the wrong choice in 1967.

Ott's transformation law T' = γT is not optional. It is required by:

- Landauer's principle (information-energy bound)
- Entropy invariance (microstate counting)
- Free energy transformation (thermodynamic consistency)
- Partition function invariance (equilibrium statistics)
- 4-vector structure (relativistic geometry)

With Ott in place:

- Jacobson's derivation becomes automatically covariant
- Connes-Rovelli thermal time works in all frames
- CMC foliation emerges from thermal equilibrium
- Shape Dynamics connects to thermodynamic spacetime
- The entire framework compiles

**General relativity is the equation of state of spacetime.**

We didn't modify this insight. We completed it.

